01:05.926 --> 01:08.093
[ Skitters screeching ]

01:13.400 --> 01:16.601
[ Indistinct shouting ]

01:16.653 --> 01:18.820
[ Skitters hissing ]

01:18.856 --> 01:19.856
You got it?
Man: Yeah.

01:19.857 --> 01:22.357
You got it?!
I got it!

01:22.409 --> 01:24.526
[ Shouting continues ]

01:28.615 --> 01:29.865
We can't stay here!

01:29.917 --> 01:31.366
Man: Can we get
some help, please?

01:31.418 --> 01:34.369
Rob: We can't go out there,
Isabella.

01:34.421 --> 01:36.955
We have no food, no water.
We're gonna starve!

01:36.957 --> 01:38.957
Do you think
you have to tell me that?

01:38.959 --> 01:41.376
Look, if we stay here,
we're dead!

01:41.428 --> 01:42.677
[ Breathing heavily ]

01:42.713 --> 01:44.629
I'm leaving.

01:44.631 --> 01:45.964
Come on, guys.

01:45.966 --> 01:47.799
Rob, you're with us.

01:47.851 --> 01:50.435
She's not coming back.

01:50.470 --> 01:52.971
We just have to wait
for an opening.

01:54.441 --> 01:56.007
Rob:
I think we're clear.

01:56.043 --> 01:57.742
[ Woman breathing shakily ]

01:57.778 --> 02:01.613
[ Door creaks ]

02:01.648 --> 02:03.064
Isabella:
Come on, guys.

02:03.116 --> 02:04.816
Let's go.

02:09.823 --> 02:11.156
Let's go.

02:14.711 --> 02:15.744
[ Growls ]

02:15.796 --> 02:16.796
Skitter!

02:16.830 --> 02:18.663
[ Screams ]

02:18.715 --> 02:19.715
Hurry!

02:22.469 --> 02:23.802
[ Skitter screeches ]

02:23.837 --> 02:27.005
Go!
Hurry, all of you!

02:27.007 --> 02:28.390
[ Rumbling ]

02:28.425 --> 02:30.759
Come on!
Come on, come on!

02:35.933 --> 02:38.099
[ Screaming ]

02:43.073 --> 02:44.073
No!

02:44.074 --> 02:46.024
[ Siren chirping ]

02:46.076 --> 02:47.108
[ Tires screech ]

02:56.703 --> 02:59.671
[ Hisses, roars ]

03:04.011 --> 03:06.177
[ Both panting ]

03:12.255 --> 03:16.255
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Falling Skies 5x05 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Non-Essential Personnel</font>
Original Air Date on July 26, 2015

03:16.279 --> 03:22.779
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

03:43.967 --> 03:46.501
Hal's not here, Pope.

03:46.553 --> 03:47.752
Where is he?

03:49.056 --> 03:50.555
Pope!

03:50.590 --> 03:53.141
Pope: Check the dumpster
in the back.

04:00.517 --> 04:02.734
No.
No, no, no, no.

04:08.525 --> 04:13.611
Yeah, I-I'm trying to remember
where I put the body.

04:13.664 --> 04:14.946
Why are you
doing this?

04:14.948 --> 04:17.949
I spent <i> years</i>
risking my life for you,

04:18.000 --> 04:19.200
and what do I get?

04:19.252 --> 04:22.537
Exile, proscribed,
cut off.

04:22.589 --> 04:24.122
You didn't give us
any choice.

04:24.174 --> 04:27.625
Just like you didn't have
a choice to save Sara?

04:27.627 --> 04:30.845
Well, now <i> I'm</i> giving <i> you</i> orders,
Mason.

04:30.881 --> 04:34.549
Next stop's a playground
4 miles south, at Arbor and 2nd.

04:34.601 --> 04:35.850
Will Hal be there?

04:35.886 --> 04:38.887
I really hope
you get to him in time.

04:42.642 --> 04:43.975
We set inside?

04:43.977 --> 04:45.143
Yeah.

04:46.980 --> 04:48.780
They've been hiding out
in that neighborhood

04:48.815 --> 04:51.649
for the past few weeks,
ever since the power went down.

04:51.651 --> 04:54.035
The skitters were finally able
to weed them out.

04:54.071 --> 04:56.654
Good idea saving them.
We can use them.

04:56.656 --> 04:58.156
Did you sort them?

04:58.158 --> 04:59.657
Yep. Good to go.

04:59.659 --> 05:01.159
My name's John Pope.

05:01.211 --> 05:03.078
And this place
looks like home.

05:03.130 --> 05:05.630
Sight lines
in every direction.

05:05.665 --> 05:07.248
We've got
a lot of guns --

05:07.300 --> 05:09.217
just not enough hands
to put them in.

05:09.252 --> 05:11.336
Stay with us,
you'll survive,

05:11.338 --> 05:14.589
but we can't afford
any liabilities.

05:14.641 --> 05:17.842
That's why this man spoke
to each and every one of you

05:17.894 --> 05:19.811
before
he brought you over.

05:19.846 --> 05:23.098
He was conducting a bit of a...
stealth interview --

05:23.150 --> 05:26.067
see who can pull their weight
and who can't.

05:28.021 --> 05:29.187
Him...

05:30.073 --> 05:32.190
...him...

05:32.192 --> 05:33.274
Her...

05:33.326 --> 05:35.944
Her.

05:37.748 --> 05:39.080
You four can't fight.

05:40.834 --> 05:42.951
You've been deemed
nonessential personnel.

05:43.003 --> 05:46.371
I'm afraid I'm gonna
have to ask you to leave.

05:46.373 --> 05:50.759
The rest of you can stay,
if you want.

05:50.794 --> 05:52.927
Or you can
take your chances out there.

05:56.183 --> 05:58.216
Come on, now.

06:04.391 --> 06:05.890
I'm a nurse.

06:05.942 --> 06:08.109
You could use me.

06:09.813 --> 06:12.147
That could be useful.

06:13.700 --> 06:15.400
Well, it's got to be
a package deal.

06:18.905 --> 06:20.738
Their ship has sailed.

06:28.965 --> 06:30.965
[ Indistinct talking ]

06:34.921 --> 06:36.337
All right.

06:37.808 --> 06:39.808
All right,
let's move out, people!

06:39.843 --> 06:41.259
We're on our way
to D.C.!

06:41.311 --> 06:42.927
Let's go.

06:46.933 --> 06:49.267
[ Engine turns over ]

06:55.742 --> 06:57.692
Anthony: Let's get these carts
put in here, guys.

06:57.744 --> 06:59.360
Can I get all those tires
put up on the wall?

06:59.412 --> 07:01.362
Fortify the barrier.
Come on.

07:01.414 --> 07:03.448
[ Anthony continues
indistinctly ]

07:38.539 --> 07:41.406
[ indistinct shouting ]

07:41.458 --> 07:43.458
[ Engine revving unevenly ]

07:45.729 --> 07:49.331
Your automobile
is too loud.

07:49.333 --> 07:53.301
She's exactly as loud
as she's supposed to be.

07:53.337 --> 07:56.972
That engine purr is one
of the sexiest sounds alive.

07:57.007 --> 08:00.008
That engine's purr will
broadcast our position

08:00.010 --> 08:02.594
to anyone
within a half-mile radius.

08:02.646 --> 08:04.813
Uh, the -- the -- the
tactical value of this vehicle

08:04.848 --> 08:05.848
is minimal at best.

08:05.849 --> 08:08.517
Ohh, God. Please.

08:08.569 --> 08:11.770
Just let me enjoy this.

08:11.822 --> 08:13.855
For a minute.

08:13.857 --> 08:16.525
No more backseat driving.

08:18.529 --> 08:20.579
But I am
in the <i> front</i> seat.

08:23.033 --> 08:24.699
Man: Take cover!

08:24.752 --> 08:26.952
[ Indistinct shouting ]

08:32.708 --> 08:33.792
What the hell?!

08:41.385 --> 08:44.719
Can't get through.
Got us boxed in both sides.

08:44.721 --> 08:46.054
Where's it coming from?!

08:47.057 --> 08:48.774
There!

08:48.809 --> 08:50.642
Return fire!

08:50.694 --> 08:52.861
That balcony! Now!

09:23.844 --> 09:26.428
Why'd you stick your neck out
for those people back there?

09:28.816 --> 09:31.600
If I talked you into saving
them, they would have owed me.

09:33.854 --> 09:37.355
You're just gaining favors.
Is that it?

09:39.409 --> 09:41.660
I don't buy it.

09:41.695 --> 09:43.778
I think you're weak.

09:47.417 --> 09:50.502
There's no room for any of that
around here.

10:00.764 --> 10:02.881
Do you want to know
who I am?

10:02.933 --> 10:06.768
I'm someone
who sees it like it is.

10:06.803 --> 10:08.887
The only reason
people do things for each other

10:08.939 --> 10:11.139
is because they expect
something in return.

10:12.776 --> 10:14.693
That's why
they're here.

10:14.728 --> 10:16.444
That's why <i> I'm</i> here.

10:16.480 --> 10:18.480
This is the way
things have always worked,

10:18.532 --> 10:20.148
and that's the only truth
there is.

10:26.156 --> 10:29.541
[ Sniffs ]

10:29.576 --> 10:32.627
If I had a beer,
I'd drink to that.

10:36.133 --> 10:39.668
Since we're
talking truth...

10:39.720 --> 10:41.720
There's a man...

10:41.755 --> 10:44.089
behind that door.

10:45.809 --> 10:48.093
I put him there.

10:49.897 --> 10:55.734
His father
killed someone...

10:55.769 --> 10:59.688
very close and important
to me.

11:03.527 --> 11:05.744
So you took something important
from <i> him.</i>

11:10.867 --> 11:12.417
Tom: Pope!

11:12.452 --> 11:14.085
Pope, are you there?

11:14.121 --> 11:16.621
There's daddy now.

11:16.673 --> 11:17.839
Pope!

11:19.042 --> 11:20.042
You at the playground?

11:20.093 --> 11:22.093
[ Breathing heavily ]

11:25.882 --> 11:27.098
He's not here, is he?

11:27.134 --> 11:28.134
No.

11:28.135 --> 11:31.519
Nobody there but you.

11:31.555 --> 11:34.973
You want me to go through
what you went through?

11:35.025 --> 11:37.058
Is that it --
Hal has to die in front of me

11:37.060 --> 11:38.893
the way that Sara died
in front of you?

11:38.895 --> 11:40.612
Don't you say
that name!

11:40.647 --> 11:43.898
You don't say
that name!

11:43.900 --> 11:45.984
I'll cut his heart out
right here, right now

11:46.036 --> 11:47.736
you say that again!

11:49.623 --> 11:51.573
So Hal's still alive?

11:53.627 --> 11:54.909
Listen to me.

11:54.962 --> 11:57.579
If Hal's still alive,
it's not too late.

11:57.631 --> 11:59.080
You can still let him go.

11:59.132 --> 12:01.132
You go your way,
I go my way.

12:01.168 --> 12:04.135
It's not too late
for you.

12:04.171 --> 12:06.721
It's not too late
for <i> me?</i>

12:08.925 --> 12:11.593
Well, there you go again, Mason,
barking orders.

12:11.645 --> 12:15.764
You really have no idea how much
trouble he's in, do you?

12:18.101 --> 12:22.103
But when
you hear his voice...

12:22.155 --> 12:26.941
Then you'll see exactly how
<i>not</i> in control you really are.

12:26.994 --> 12:27.994
Pope!

12:34.785 --> 12:37.118
Wakey, wakey.

12:37.120 --> 12:38.670
[ Whistles ]

12:38.705 --> 12:40.205
That's what I always liked
about you, Hal.

12:40.257 --> 12:43.124
You got teeth.
Not afraid to bite.

12:43.176 --> 12:45.593
Go to hell, asshole.

12:47.297 --> 12:48.847
Oh, we're already there,
kid.

12:51.802 --> 12:53.018
You hear this, Tom?

12:53.053 --> 12:54.519
Pope!

12:54.554 --> 12:55.854
You hear this?

12:55.889 --> 12:58.640
Huh?!
You hear this?!

12:58.642 --> 13:00.809
[ Screaming ]

13:03.280 --> 13:04.696
Aaaah!
[ Grunts ]

13:04.731 --> 13:05.731
Yaaaah!

13:05.732 --> 13:09.034
[ Groaning ]

13:09.069 --> 13:11.119
[ Grunting loudly ]

13:13.323 --> 13:15.907
Still not too late
for me?!

13:17.911 --> 13:19.577
Tom?

13:23.750 --> 13:24.966
Tom?

13:30.173 --> 13:31.840
I'm gonna kill you.

13:35.345 --> 13:37.979
Take Arbor street
2 miles east

13:38.014 --> 13:41.099
until you come to
the urgent-care clinic.

13:41.151 --> 13:42.183
Call me then.

13:42.235 --> 13:44.235
Isabella,
find a first-aid kit

13:44.271 --> 13:46.905
and make sure
he doesn't bleed out.

13:51.778 --> 13:53.328
Man: Go, go!

13:53.363 --> 13:55.196
[ Gunfire ]

13:58.201 --> 14:00.118
Keep your head down!

14:00.170 --> 14:02.087
Man:
We want the pickup truck

14:02.122 --> 14:05.874
and half your weapons
and ammo -- now!

14:05.926 --> 14:08.042
That's not happening!

14:08.095 --> 14:10.345
Give us what we want,

14:10.380 --> 14:14.182
or we take out a vehicle
every 30 seconds!

14:14.217 --> 14:16.217
Your choice!

14:16.219 --> 14:19.888
30, 29, 28...

14:19.890 --> 14:21.356
They only asked
for one vehicle.

14:21.391 --> 14:23.141
That could mean there's not
that many of them up there.

14:23.193 --> 14:25.276
They are in
a tactically superior position,

14:25.312 --> 14:26.895
and they are concealed.

14:26.947 --> 14:29.030
A frontal assault
will result in heavy casualties.

14:29.065 --> 14:30.899
...22, 21... - Okay, we can't risk
any more casualties.

14:30.951 --> 14:32.901
Let's just give them
our damn ammo.

14:32.903 --> 14:35.203
So they can turn around and shoot
us in the back with our own bullets?

14:35.238 --> 14:36.988
I'm going in.

14:37.040 --> 14:38.907
I'm gonna talk them down.
That's what I'm gonna do.

14:38.909 --> 14:40.325
That's suicide.

14:40.377 --> 14:42.677
We can't lose our ammo,
and we can't lose our vehicle.

14:42.712 --> 14:45.046
But, Dan,
we can't lose you.

14:45.081 --> 14:46.748
Well, you haven't.

14:46.800 --> 14:48.082
And you won't.

14:48.084 --> 14:49.084
Man: ...7, 6...

14:49.085 --> 14:51.386
2nd Mass, stand down!

14:51.421 --> 14:53.638
...3, 2, 1!

14:53.673 --> 14:55.423
Don't shoot!
Time's up!

14:57.093 --> 15:02.096
I want to talk for my people,
face-to-face.

15:04.768 --> 15:06.684
I'm unarmed.

15:08.772 --> 15:10.238
Okay?

15:10.273 --> 15:13.107
Hey! St-- stand down!
I said stand down, everybody!

15:14.861 --> 15:17.412
One more step,
and you die!

15:17.447 --> 15:19.364
We're gonna...

15:19.416 --> 15:21.332
We're not gonna be firing
at you.

15:21.368 --> 15:25.286
There'll be no more gunshots
from us.

15:25.288 --> 15:27.922
Just me -- walking.

15:27.958 --> 15:29.374
Here I am.

15:29.426 --> 15:31.793
I'm unarmed and...

15:31.845 --> 15:33.928
[ Door creaks ]

15:35.465 --> 15:36.465
Okay.

15:38.268 --> 15:40.969
I'm coming in.

15:40.971 --> 15:43.137
Hello?

15:43.190 --> 15:44.739
Guys, stand down.

15:49.813 --> 15:52.146
[ Door creaks ]

15:58.321 --> 15:59.321
Wha--

16:01.908 --> 16:04.242
Man: I've got your man!

16:04.294 --> 16:06.628
He's injured.
Do you want him back?

16:06.663 --> 16:10.131
Start stacking guns and ammo
against the door.

16:10.167 --> 16:12.717
You give us proof
he's alive!

16:12.753 --> 16:15.587
Or we're coming
the hell in!

16:15.639 --> 16:18.840
<i>One</i> person comes to see.

16:30.404 --> 16:31.486
[ Door creaks ]

16:31.521 --> 16:32.771
That's enough.

16:34.941 --> 16:36.608
He's hurt.

16:36.660 --> 16:38.493
I'm a doctor.
Let me --

16:38.528 --> 16:39.744
I don't care.

16:39.780 --> 16:41.413
You're surrounded.

16:41.448 --> 16:42.947
We can overrun you.

16:42.949 --> 16:45.617
No. You won't.

16:45.619 --> 16:48.703
Anne, I got this.

16:48.755 --> 16:50.789
Tell her
what you told me.

16:54.845 --> 16:56.878
I got a wife...

16:59.299 --> 17:02.717
...two sons...In here.

17:02.769 --> 17:05.185
I need more guns and ammo
to protect them,

17:05.222 --> 17:07.771
and I need your truck
to get the hell out of here.

17:07.808 --> 17:10.858
And if I think they're in danger
for even a second...

17:12.979 --> 17:14.561
...your husband's dead.

17:16.900 --> 17:19.401
Anne,<i> honey...</i>

17:21.238 --> 17:23.738
...I'm telling you --
I got this.

17:23.790 --> 17:25.240
[ Gun cocks ]
[ Gasps ]

17:25.291 --> 17:27.208
Easy.
Okay. Okay.

17:27.243 --> 17:28.576
Easy.

17:29.996 --> 17:31.830
[ Door creaks ]

17:31.832 --> 17:34.883
Here we are.

17:34.918 --> 17:37.719
[ Breathing heavily ]

17:37.754 --> 17:39.754
He's alive,
but he's hurt.

17:39.806 --> 17:41.339
There's only one gunman.

17:41.341 --> 17:42.674
Then we're moving in?
No.

17:42.676 --> 17:44.759
He says he's doing this
to protect his family.

17:44.811 --> 17:46.561
He's got a wife
and a couple of kids.

17:46.596 --> 17:48.480
Weaver says
he's got this.

17:48.515 --> 17:51.516
We're gonna trust him --
for the moment.

17:51.568 --> 17:53.518
[ Breathing heavily ]

17:55.655 --> 17:58.022
Gunman: Move.

17:58.024 --> 17:59.657
Move!

18:01.862 --> 18:05.029
All right, stop. Sit down.
Hands behind your head.

18:10.670 --> 18:12.504
[ Groans ]

18:14.291 --> 18:16.708
Well, that's great.

18:19.930 --> 18:21.713
[ Clears throat ]

18:23.884 --> 18:25.383
Give me the knife.

18:25.435 --> 18:28.019
It's not gonna take long.
I got to fix my arm.

18:28.054 --> 18:30.889
That's the only thing
that's gonna happen here.

18:30.941 --> 18:32.690
Give me the knife <i> now.</i>

18:35.729 --> 18:38.696
[ Groaning ]

18:41.451 --> 18:43.985
You want to die?
Do you?

18:51.461 --> 18:52.627
Whoa!

18:52.662 --> 18:55.330
[ Gasping ]

18:56.750 --> 18:58.583
Look like
you've been through hell.

18:58.635 --> 19:00.802
Yeah, thanks to
a couple cops.

19:00.837 --> 19:02.387
Cops?

19:02.422 --> 19:04.639
Two guys in a cop car, anyway --
police Bronco.

19:04.674 --> 19:05.890
What did they look like?

19:05.926 --> 19:07.475
One guy was bald,
the other black.

19:07.511 --> 19:08.977
They have a prisoner
with them --

19:09.012 --> 19:10.595
young guy,
dark hair, mid 20s?

19:10.597 --> 19:12.013
I didn't see
anyone like that.

19:15.018 --> 19:16.768
[ Sighs ]
What happened?

19:16.770 --> 19:19.737
We were pinned by some skitters
in one of the ghettos.

19:19.773 --> 19:21.856
Those two guys...
Rescued us.

19:21.908 --> 19:24.075
Then they started
picking people out,

19:24.110 --> 19:26.070
choosing who they thought
would be useful to them.

19:27.414 --> 19:28.780
We didn't make
the cut.

19:28.782 --> 19:30.498
The rest of them, though,
they're with him.

19:30.534 --> 19:31.783
How many
does he have with him?

19:31.785 --> 19:34.335
Including
the guy he came with, 11.

19:34.371 --> 19:36.621
He said he was gonna
arm them all.

19:40.460 --> 19:41.960
You're going after
that guy?

19:42.012 --> 19:44.095
He's got my son.

19:44.130 --> 19:46.431
Where was the last place
you saw him?

19:46.466 --> 19:48.800
[ Grunts,
inhales sharply ]

19:48.852 --> 19:50.468
Come on.
At least say something.

19:50.520 --> 19:53.972
I've been trying to talk to you
for the past 20 minutes.

19:53.974 --> 19:56.641
I overheard you
when you were outside.

19:56.643 --> 20:00.144
Those people
Pope made you leave behind --

20:00.146 --> 20:02.697
I think that you stuck
your neck out for them

20:02.732 --> 20:04.449
because you care.

20:04.484 --> 20:07.619
And yeah,
you're playing it cool, calm,

20:07.654 --> 20:09.120
but I can tell
you're scared.

20:09.155 --> 20:11.573
You have to
stop talking.

20:11.625 --> 20:14.125
[ Chuckling ] Oh.
She speaks.

20:14.160 --> 20:16.494
She wants me to shut up --
maybe 'cause I'm telling her

20:16.546 --> 20:17.912
the truth
she doesn't want to hear.

20:17.964 --> 20:19.664
You don't know
what you're talking about.

20:19.716 --> 20:20.832
I've got it
under control.

20:20.884 --> 20:22.166
No. You don't.

20:22.168 --> 20:23.668
He's insane.

20:23.720 --> 20:25.053
Trust me on that.

20:25.088 --> 20:26.504
Yeah.

20:26.556 --> 20:30.174
The more crazy and brutal
they are,

20:30.176 --> 20:33.678
the longer
they stay in charge.

20:33.680 --> 20:35.013
Wow.

20:35.065 --> 20:38.182
I feel sorry for you
if you actually believe that.

20:38.184 --> 20:40.151
I believe enough of it.

20:42.105 --> 20:43.521
[ Zipper closes ]

20:43.573 --> 20:45.607
I'm sorry
this is happening to you.

20:45.659 --> 20:47.108
Right.

20:47.160 --> 20:48.660
I'll feel sorry for <i> you</i>

20:48.695 --> 20:51.029
when Pope finds out
you're not a nurse.

20:53.450 --> 20:55.950
I got a 13-year-old brother
can stitch better than that.

20:56.002 --> 20:57.118
I was a bit rushed.

20:57.170 --> 20:59.754
Bullshit.
You're not a nurse.

20:59.789 --> 21:02.173
You think he's not
gonna figure that out?

21:03.510 --> 21:06.511
Listen to me. I can get you
to my people safely.

21:06.546 --> 21:07.845
If Pope is pr--

21:09.466 --> 21:11.799
If Pope what?

21:13.770 --> 21:16.554
He's trying
to make me let him go.

21:16.556 --> 21:18.606
Is that right?

21:18.642 --> 21:20.642
He putting up
a good argument?

21:22.646 --> 21:23.895
No.

21:27.067 --> 21:29.233
Been a day and a half.

21:29.235 --> 21:31.986
You haven't had
a single drink of water.

21:32.038 --> 21:34.072
You got to be thirsty
as all hell, brother.

21:53.893 --> 21:57.595
You know, if and when we beat
these alien sons of bitches

21:57.597 --> 21:59.013
and have to rebuild
society,

21:59.065 --> 22:00.765
I think
your daddy wants the job.

22:00.817 --> 22:02.600
Leader
of the new world.

22:02.602 --> 22:04.235
You have no idea
what you're talking about.

22:04.270 --> 22:05.486
Is that right?

22:05.522 --> 22:06.854
Well,
Volm are out there

22:06.906 --> 22:10.108
broadcasting his orders
all over the country.

22:10.110 --> 22:12.910
I'd say he's lining up
the gig to <i> me.</i>

22:21.254 --> 22:22.870
You know, Hal,

22:22.922 --> 22:24.789
when two guys sit down
and have a drink together,

22:24.791 --> 22:26.674
usually,
they see eye-to-eye.

22:30.013 --> 22:32.096
I'll give you
a sip of water.

22:32.132 --> 22:34.549
Then all you got to do
is admit it --

22:34.601 --> 22:36.684
I mean,
it looks convenient.

22:36.720 --> 22:38.136
That's all.

22:39.272 --> 22:43.024
You can give me a drink
if you want.

22:43.059 --> 22:46.811
'Cause I would love to spit it
back in your damn face.

22:53.820 --> 22:55.953
[ Groaning ]

22:55.989 --> 22:57.622
Why can't you see it?

22:57.657 --> 22:58.906
Why can't you see?

22:58.958 --> 23:00.625
[ Groans ]

23:00.660 --> 23:05.663
I need you to see
what I've seen for three years.

23:05.665 --> 23:07.165
Don't you understand?

23:07.217 --> 23:09.717
If people trust Tom Mason,
more people are gonna die.

23:09.753 --> 23:11.586
Why can't you see that?

23:11.638 --> 23:13.755
[ Gasping ]

23:13.807 --> 23:15.056
[ Groans ]

23:15.091 --> 23:17.558
He's gotten
so many people killed.

23:17.594 --> 23:18.676
Just admit that.

23:18.728 --> 23:20.928
Say that, Hal.
Say that.

23:20.980 --> 23:23.848
Say "he's gotten
so many people killed."

23:23.850 --> 23:24.850
Say it.

23:24.851 --> 23:27.819
[ Groans ]

23:27.854 --> 23:29.353
Say it.
Say the words.

23:29.355 --> 23:31.189
Say the words "he's gotten
so many people killed."

23:31.241 --> 23:32.774
[ Groans ]

23:32.826 --> 23:35.159
Say it. Say it.

23:35.195 --> 23:37.862
Say the words!

23:37.864 --> 23:40.698
Say the words!
Just say the goddamn words, Hal!

23:40.750 --> 23:41.866
Just say it!

23:43.036 --> 23:45.253
You say it,
you son of a bitch!

23:45.288 --> 23:48.873
We'd all be dead
if it wasn't for him!

23:48.925 --> 23:51.843
If you think that you're
a victim and he's the enemy,

23:51.878 --> 23:53.878
you've lost
your goddamn mind!

23:53.880 --> 23:54.880
[ Gun cocks ]

23:54.931 --> 23:56.714
Fine! Do it!

23:56.766 --> 23:57.849
Coward!

24:10.486 --> 24:13.321
[ Gunfire, creature screeches,
indistinct shouting ]

24:18.911 --> 24:21.462
[ Breathing heavily ]

24:21.497 --> 24:23.881
[ Groaning ]

24:23.916 --> 24:27.335
[ Gunfire, shouting continue ]

24:27.387 --> 24:29.136
Anthony:
Everyone on high alert!

24:29.172 --> 24:31.339
What happened?
Hornet attack.

24:31.341 --> 24:33.057
How many?
Just one.

24:33.092 --> 24:35.760
One? Nine of you
couldn't take out one bug?

24:35.812 --> 24:38.012
No. This was bigger --
thicker.

24:38.014 --> 24:39.480
I'm telling you, man,
it wouldn't go down,

24:39.515 --> 24:41.432
like it was on steroids
or something.

24:41.484 --> 24:43.818
[ Groaning ]

24:43.853 --> 24:44.853
Can he walk?

24:44.854 --> 24:46.487
Oh, God!
I don't know.

24:46.522 --> 24:48.489
What do you mean you don't know?
Can he fight or not?

24:48.524 --> 24:50.204
I don't know. I just need
more time to ex--

24:55.248 --> 24:56.947
No liabilities.

25:04.173 --> 25:06.340
Bury him out back.

25:15.268 --> 25:17.101
Rebecca: Tom.

25:17.136 --> 25:19.220
You have to stop.

25:19.222 --> 25:21.222
No, no, no, no.
I don't have time for this.

25:21.224 --> 25:22.473
I got to get my son.

25:22.525 --> 25:23.974
We can't let you
risk your life.

25:24.027 --> 25:25.393
Why? Tell me.

25:25.395 --> 25:27.061
No more cryptic bullshit.
No more metaphors.

25:27.063 --> 25:28.063
Just tell me.

25:28.064 --> 25:30.948
If you die...

25:30.983 --> 25:33.117
The entire war
will be lost.

25:33.152 --> 25:35.286
What are you talking about?
We're winning.

25:35.321 --> 25:36.821
We're kicking
their ass.

25:36.873 --> 25:38.239
It won't last.

25:39.876 --> 25:41.242
The Espheni will rebuild,

25:41.244 --> 25:43.911
as they've done with
countless civilizations before.

25:43.913 --> 25:45.463
In a year,

25:45.498 --> 25:48.049
it will be as if none
of your victories ever happened.

25:50.136 --> 25:52.586
We're creating
a new weapon

25:52.588 --> 25:56.257
that may finally
wipe them out forever.

25:56.309 --> 25:58.592
But we need <i> you,</i>
Tom --

25:58.594 --> 26:01.262
<i>only</i> you, no one else --
to deliver it.

26:01.314 --> 26:04.432
If you die...

26:04.434 --> 26:07.068
Everything will be lost.

26:07.103 --> 26:08.819
You know
what you're asking me to do?

26:08.855 --> 26:10.020
Just leave my son
inside?

26:10.073 --> 26:11.522
Sacrifice him
to the greater good?

26:13.192 --> 26:15.409
No. Not this time.
Not anymore.

26:15.445 --> 26:17.194
Tom. I love you.

26:18.614 --> 26:20.498
You're not Rebecca.

26:24.454 --> 26:27.922
Can't believe we're giving up
half our ammo.

26:27.957 --> 26:31.175
Man:
Yeah, it's a death wish.

26:42.522 --> 26:44.105
Your family back there?

26:48.060 --> 26:49.643
Those your kids' drawings,
huh?

26:58.621 --> 27:00.621
[ Groans ]

27:00.656 --> 27:02.456
I have children, too.

27:04.377 --> 27:06.327
Well...

27:06.329 --> 27:09.413
<i>Had,</i> I guess.

27:09.465 --> 27:11.248
Both daughters.

27:11.300 --> 27:14.969
What do you mean,
"had"?

27:15.004 --> 27:18.305
I mean they're dead.

27:20.092 --> 27:21.926
Was this
during the invasion?

27:24.013 --> 27:27.097
One during and one...

27:29.435 --> 27:31.519
...after.

27:33.189 --> 27:37.024
You would have done anything
to protect them.

27:37.076 --> 27:38.576
So you understand.

27:41.364 --> 27:43.080
Why are you looking
back there?

27:45.117 --> 27:46.917
You think
they need your help?

27:46.953 --> 27:48.202
They're fine.

27:50.089 --> 27:52.339
They don't need
anybody else.

27:52.375 --> 27:53.674
I'm their father.

27:56.045 --> 27:58.345
They're safe with me.

27:58.381 --> 27:59.680
Understand?

28:01.017 --> 28:03.217
Yeah. I do.

28:03.269 --> 28:05.219
[ Tap on window ]
Man: All right, that's it.

28:05.271 --> 28:07.021
That's the last of it.

28:07.056 --> 28:09.273
Well...

28:09.308 --> 28:11.392
I guess
that's all of it.

28:15.398 --> 28:18.699
If -- if...

28:18.734 --> 28:21.285
If I let you go, they're just
gonna barge in here

28:21.320 --> 28:22.987
and take everything back.

28:23.039 --> 28:25.239
Wait a minute.
We had a deal.

28:25.241 --> 28:26.540
We <i> don't.</i>

28:28.211 --> 28:31.212
You think I'm stupid?

28:31.247 --> 28:33.414
No, I don't think
you're stupid.

28:33.416 --> 28:37.635
Leave the keys in the pickup
and move south!

28:37.670 --> 28:41.088
Do not stop!

28:41.140 --> 28:43.757
I'll let him go in a day,
and he'll catch up!

28:45.595 --> 28:48.429
Crazy son of a bitch.

28:48.481 --> 28:49.730
[ Sighs ]

28:49.765 --> 28:51.265
All right, fine.

28:51.317 --> 28:53.267
We're gonna go south,
like he wants,

28:53.319 --> 28:55.069
but then
we're doubling back,

28:55.104 --> 28:58.989
and we're getting Weaver
the hell out of there.

28:59.025 --> 29:02.243
Hal:
What happened out there?

29:02.278 --> 29:04.078
Hornet attacked.

29:04.113 --> 29:05.362
Ken broke his ankle,

29:05.414 --> 29:07.364
so Pope shot him
right in front of me.

29:07.416 --> 29:09.416
Writing's on the wall.
You can see that.

29:09.452 --> 29:11.118
If you stay here,
you're dead.

29:11.170 --> 29:12.620
I know.

29:12.672 --> 29:14.455
That's why I'm leaving.

29:14.457 --> 29:16.173
You are?

29:16.208 --> 29:18.509
Yeah, staying with Pope
was never part of the plan.

29:21.797 --> 29:24.632
He gave it to me
a couple of hours ago.

29:24.684 --> 29:26.467
While he was
doing that...

29:28.187 --> 29:30.554
...I borrowed these.

29:30.606 --> 29:33.274
I told you
I had it under control.

29:33.309 --> 29:35.526
He put all the guns
in the paint shop.

29:35.561 --> 29:38.312
That's my last stop before I get
the hell out of here.

29:38.314 --> 29:41.732
Well,
color me impressed.

29:41.784 --> 29:44.568
So,
you gonna release me?

29:44.620 --> 29:45.620
[ Scoffs ]

29:45.621 --> 29:47.621
You still don't trust me?

29:47.657 --> 29:49.456
Of course not.

29:51.327 --> 29:53.127
The 2nd Mass will take you in.
We're good people.

29:53.162 --> 29:55.079
If you can read me half as well
as you can read Pope,

29:55.131 --> 29:56.380
you know
I'm telling you the truth.

29:56.415 --> 29:57.665
I've been with good people
before.

29:57.667 --> 29:59.500
Well, we're different.

29:59.502 --> 30:01.168
<i>Everyone</i> says
they're different.

30:01.170 --> 30:03.754
We're putting the world back
the way that it used to be,

30:03.806 --> 30:06.507
and we're doing that
by being there for each other.

30:06.559 --> 30:08.519
That's how we started.
That's how we're gonna end.

30:11.347 --> 30:13.847
Man: I have a few more
if you need them.

30:29.832 --> 30:32.866
Just right over here.
You can just set it down.

30:37.256 --> 30:39.707
Right here.

30:39.759 --> 30:41.458
Over there.

30:55.191 --> 30:57.274
[ Shouts indistinctly ]

30:59.645 --> 31:01.395
Man #2: Clear!

31:22.718 --> 31:24.718
[ Indistinct shouting
in distance ]

31:57.199 --> 31:58.782
Ready?

32:01.787 --> 32:04.037
All right.

32:04.089 --> 32:06.123
[ Indistinct shouting
in distance ]

32:13.215 --> 32:14.047
[ Gasps ]

32:14.049 --> 32:15.049
Aah!

32:17.720 --> 32:18.552
[ Groans ]

32:18.604 --> 32:21.021
[ Indistinct shouting ]

32:21.857 --> 32:23.557
Aah! Aah!

32:23.609 --> 32:25.692
Man: We have a breach
in the perimeter!

32:26.896 --> 32:28.145
Man #2:
How many are there?

32:28.197 --> 32:30.697
Dad!

32:30.733 --> 32:33.066
Over that way!
By the truck!

32:33.068 --> 32:34.535
Get out of here!

32:34.570 --> 32:36.069
Man: Go, go, go, go!
There he is!

32:50.803 --> 32:54.221
[ Screaming ]

32:59.094 --> 33:01.845
Come on! Come on!
We got to go!

33:01.897 --> 33:02.897
[ Engine turns over ]

33:02.898 --> 33:04.982
[ Engine revs ]

33:07.937 --> 33:09.820
Gunman: If we stick together,
we're one.

33:09.855 --> 33:11.772
We are one --

33:11.824 --> 33:13.106
what's our motto?

33:14.276 --> 33:15.909
What's our motto?

33:15.945 --> 33:17.110
[ Door opens ]

33:21.667 --> 33:23.116
Everything all right
in there?

33:33.846 --> 33:36.680
Hey,
I could use some water.

33:46.976 --> 33:47.976
Thank you.

33:55.034 --> 33:56.149
Put down the rifle.

33:58.954 --> 34:00.737
Put it down.

34:05.578 --> 34:07.578
Take it easy.

34:08.797 --> 34:12.632
It's not happening.

34:30.853 --> 34:33.270
Maggie: Okay.

34:33.322 --> 34:34.821
I'll go first.

34:38.911 --> 34:40.159
Ohh.

34:40.195 --> 34:41.195
God!

34:41.196 --> 34:42.196
Hey. You okay?

34:42.197 --> 34:44.947
[ Breathing heavily ]

34:56.295 --> 34:59.179
[ Groans ]

34:59.214 --> 35:01.632
Do you feel that?
That rush?

35:01.684 --> 35:03.634
Yeah, all I could
think about...

35:03.686 --> 35:05.302
[ Breathing heavily ]

35:05.354 --> 35:07.220
Why is this
happening now?

35:07.272 --> 35:09.856
I don't know. Maybe it's --
it's the -- it's the adrenaline.

35:09.892 --> 35:12.225
God, I hate
not being in control.

35:12.227 --> 35:13.810
I can't take it anymore.

35:13.862 --> 35:15.145
[ Voice breaking ]
I hate it.

35:15.197 --> 35:16.697
Me too.

35:16.732 --> 35:17.981
Okay.

35:18.033 --> 35:20.400
Just focus.

35:26.075 --> 35:29.660
How long you think
you can hold that gun steady?

35:31.797 --> 35:32.913
Back away!

35:32.965 --> 35:36.750
Ben, Maggie, stop.
Stand down.

35:36.752 --> 35:38.969
Easy, friend.

35:39.004 --> 35:40.837
Easy.

35:40.889 --> 35:43.006
What do you want
from us?

35:44.727 --> 35:45.842
We want to help you.

35:45.894 --> 35:47.260
I don't need your help.

35:47.312 --> 35:50.097
My family
doesn't need your help.

35:50.149 --> 35:52.399
I've been looking
into your eyes,

35:52.434 --> 35:56.687
and I see the same look
that I had when I lost my --

35:56.739 --> 35:57.904
my children.

35:59.358 --> 36:00.358
Hey, man.

36:02.861 --> 36:04.828
And it's not just me.

36:04.863 --> 36:07.280
It's not just me.

36:07.282 --> 36:09.916
My friend out there --
she just lost her little girl

36:09.952 --> 36:12.085
three months ago --
his sister.

36:16.091 --> 36:18.175
I've been where you've been,
brother.

36:18.210 --> 36:22.796
I walked those dark roads --
every single one of them.

36:24.133 --> 36:26.933
And I wouldn't be standing
in front of you right now

36:26.969 --> 36:30.303
if it wasn't
for my people.

36:30.355 --> 36:33.106
We call ourselves
the 2nd Mass.

36:33.142 --> 36:39.279
When I lost my girls,
they were there for me.

36:39.314 --> 36:40.447
I was lucky.

36:40.482 --> 36:42.699
If they hadn't been,
I'd be <i> you --</i>

36:42.735 --> 36:44.818
standing there now,
just like you.

36:46.405 --> 36:50.157
There's not that many of us
left, is there?

36:50.209 --> 36:54.127
And now we need each other
more than ever.

36:54.163 --> 36:55.829
And when we win
this war --

36:55.831 --> 36:58.165
we're <i> gonna</i> win this war!
We're gonna win it.

36:58.217 --> 37:01.084
And the people
that we're gonna lean on,

37:01.136 --> 37:05.055
they're not necessarily
gonna be our blood,

37:05.090 --> 37:06.339
but they're gonna be
family.

37:09.011 --> 37:11.178
They're gonna...

37:11.230 --> 37:14.981
They're gonna be family.

37:15.017 --> 37:16.483
They have to be.

37:16.518 --> 37:20.437
We've all lost
so many.

37:20.489 --> 37:23.523
And I don't see
that we have any other choice.

37:23.525 --> 37:24.825
Do you?

37:32.868 --> 37:34.534
I know you.

37:37.790 --> 37:39.840
I know you.

37:39.875 --> 37:42.926
Do you understand?

37:42.961 --> 37:46.379
You're not
the only one.

37:46.431 --> 37:49.049
You're not
the only one.

37:57.893 --> 37:59.309
What's behind that door?

38:34.396 --> 38:35.896
My God.

38:35.931 --> 38:37.564
Gunman: I got the skitters
that did this.

38:37.599 --> 38:39.432
[ Breathing shakily ]

38:39.434 --> 38:42.435
[ Voice breaking ]
At least I did that.

38:42.487 --> 38:45.105
Right, baby?

38:45.157 --> 38:48.275
I was too l-late.

38:48.277 --> 38:52.612
But at --
at least I did that.

38:54.950 --> 38:57.918
My baby.

38:57.953 --> 39:01.204
My baby.

39:01.256 --> 39:03.340
My baby!

39:03.375 --> 39:05.508
[ Wailing ]

39:11.133 --> 39:15.101
My baby!

39:15.137 --> 39:17.971
[ Wailing continues ]

39:27.528 --> 39:31.864
I think the second he mentioned
his family, I knew.

39:31.916 --> 39:33.499
Looking at him,

39:33.534 --> 39:39.421
it's like seeing myself
after I lost Jeanne.

39:39.457 --> 39:43.625
Or like seeing <i> you</i>
after you lost Lexi.

39:46.497 --> 39:48.764
We can't just
leave him here.

39:48.799 --> 39:50.766
He needs our help.

39:52.386 --> 39:53.469
[ Sighs ]

39:53.471 --> 39:55.637
He tried to kill you,
Dan.

39:55.639 --> 39:58.807
Well...

39:58.859 --> 40:01.560
Hey,
you were there for <i> me.</i>

40:01.612 --> 40:04.530
I'm trying to be there
for <i> you.</i>

40:06.400 --> 40:11.036
If we just leave him
to wither away,

40:11.072 --> 40:13.655
what does that say
about us?

40:15.576 --> 40:18.877
I think we have a good shot
at helping this guy out.

40:22.550 --> 40:23.999
I get it.

40:25.753 --> 40:27.719
...honey.

40:27.755 --> 40:29.838
[ Chuckles ]

40:34.595 --> 40:36.428
All right.

40:43.521 --> 40:45.070
Never got your name.

40:46.657 --> 40:47.940
Marty.

40:49.860 --> 40:51.827
Marty.

40:51.862 --> 40:53.028
Daniel.

40:58.752 --> 41:02.121
Isabella: How many more times
do we need to circle this area?

41:02.173 --> 41:04.957
Hal: As many as it takes.
I got to find my dad.

41:06.710 --> 41:08.710
You know, I can't believe
it's taken me this long

41:08.712 --> 41:10.462
to say this,
but thank you --

41:10.514 --> 41:12.181
for getting me
out of there.

41:12.216 --> 41:14.683
[ Chuckles ]

41:14.718 --> 41:16.552
You got <i> yourself</i> out.

41:16.604 --> 41:18.554
It was
something you said.

41:18.606 --> 41:20.439
Yeah? What was that?

41:20.474 --> 41:22.024
That everything
starts and ends

41:22.059 --> 41:24.026
with just being there
for each other.

41:27.698 --> 41:30.566
My dad used to say
something similar.

41:30.618 --> 41:33.819
And then I realized all I was
talking about was surviving.

41:33.871 --> 41:35.954
And all you were talking about
was living.

41:39.743 --> 41:41.793
[ Chuckles lightly ]

41:48.252 --> 41:50.135
Pope.

41:52.089 --> 41:53.589
John.

41:56.760 --> 41:58.093
